=head1 DESCRIPTION

Well-formed data on a contact, used by agents to complete a contact
request. You can have up to 4,096 UTF-8 bytes across all references for
a contact.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Arn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the reference


=head2 Status => Str

Status of the attachment reference type.


=head2 StatusReason => Str

Relevant details why the reference was not successfully created.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Type => Str

The type of the reference. C<DATE> must be of type Epoch timestamp.


=head2 Value => Str

A valid value for the reference. For example, for a URL reference, a
formatted URL that is displayed to an agent in the Contact Control
Panel (CCP).



